      "official_event": true,
      "description_long": "This September festival celebrates the traditional art of anchovy preservation. After 40-60 days of curing in salt-filled chestnut barrels, the anchovies are ready to be enjoyed. The salting process is a traditional method that has preserved this delicacy for generations. Festival-goers can taste salted anchovies prepared in various ways - with oil, oregano, and garlic, or simply with warm bread and Cinque Terre wine. Food stalls offer anchovy-based dishes, cooking demonstrations show traditional preparation methods, and the event celebrates the maritime culture of Monterosso.",
